programme.title: ATP 250 Houston: 1/2 finale (2x)
programme.desc: Čeprav bo glavnina peščenega dela sezone potekala v Evropi, bodo nekateri igralci na oranžno podlago presedlali že v Houstonu, kjer bo na sporedu turnir serije 250. Pred letom dni se je zmage veselil Juan Monaco, letos pa so domačini očitno odločeni, da zmaga ostane doma, saj je med prvimi osmimi nosilci kar pet Američanov. Prvi nosilec bo Jack Sock

programme.title: Spanish league: Ademar Leon - Barcelona
programme.desc: Liga Asobal je najvišje klubsko rokometno tekmovanje v Španiji. Igra se po pravilih EHF-a, v njej trenutno nastopa 16 klubov. Ustanovljena je bila leta 1958 pod imenom Divizija časti (Division de Honor). Preimenovala se je leta 1990, ko je dobila današnje ime. programme.title: West Bromwich Albion v Liverpool
programme.desc: Liverpool can ill afford any slip-ups in the chase for a Champions League slot but West Brom can cause them real problems. It's understandable that the Baggies have stalled since passing the 40-point safety mark. Their tiny squad is exhausted. Tony Pulis has worked miracles and needs the reward of a treasure chest of summer transfer funds. This is also the sort of game to kick-start a new charge for a club record Premier League points haul. They are so strong in the air at set pieces. Liverpool can't defend them or keep clean sheets. I expect a draw

programme.title: Football today
programme.desc: Brought to you By Renegades

programme.title: Manchester United v Chelsea
programme.desc: On paper it's one of the biggest fixtures of the season, but there are factors to suggest that this won't be a United-Chelsea classic. A close one as with last month's FA Cup tie? Almost certainly. End to end attacking excitement? Probably not. Chelsea will be fresher than United and quite frankly are much the better team right now, so Jose Mourinho is unlikely to set his side up for an open game. Moreover, he'll be very keen to avoid any prospect of a third defeat of the season to his old side - and maybe more pertinently to Antonio Conte. A fourth Old Trafford Premier League draw in a row will be a popular prediction

programme.title: Aviva Prem: Northampton v Saracens
programme.desc: Northampton Saints have narrowly lost their last two Aviva Premiership Rugby matches very late on, against Leicester and Wasps. The Saints have played six previous matches at stadiummk with a won two lost one record there in the European Cup and an identical record there in Premiership Rugby. Saracens only defeat in their last six first team matches was 10-32 at home to Leicester in the semi-final of the Anglo-Welsh Cup on 11 March. Saracens have lost three of their last five away games in Premiership Rugby, at visits to Bath, Worcester and Gloucester. Saracens have played three previous matches in Milton Keynes winning the two home games they moved there from Vicarage Road, against Bristol in 2008 and Northampton in 2012, but losing 20-25 there in a Saints home game in 2015. Saracens only loss in their last five matches against Northampton in all tournaments was 15-20 at Allianz Park in Premiership Rugby in March 2016

programme.title: Ross County v Celtic
programme.desc: Ross County skipper Andrew Davies is rated as 50-50 for the visit of Celtic due to a back problem. Jay McEveley, Tony Dingwall, Ian McShane, Paul Quinn and Chris Burke are not yet fit, Martin Woods is suspended but Jim O'Brien returns after a ban. Leigh Griffiths is back in the Celtic squad after recovering from a bone fracture in his back. Boss Brendan Rodgers reported a couple of minor fitness concerns in unnamed players ahead of Sunday's trip. County go into the match three points clear of the relegation play-off spot and three behind seventh-placed Kilmarnock

programme.title: F1: Bahrain Grand Prix
programme.desc: A year ago, they big question ahead of each grand prix weekend was how big the gap would be between Mercedes and the rest of the field. There were races where the strengths of the Red Bull or Ferrari might mean there was a chance a battle would brew at the front of the field, but Mercedes entered every round as the undisputable favourite. No longer. This weekend in Bahrain there are several reasons why Ferrari should be seen as the favourites. The 5.4km track rewards power but also requires good traction out of slow corners. With just a sample of two races it's hard to determine which car that will suit more, but the hotter temperatures (the mercury is expected to tip 40C during the day this week) are likely to favour Ferrari
